	\section{Research Objectives and Questions}
    \label{sec:objectives}
	
	The overarching aim of this thesis is to design, implement, and evaluate a knowledge-grounded, RAG-based multimodal system that supports dental radiograph analysis, diagnosis, and treatment recommendation, with particular emphasis on applicability in resource constrained clinical environments such as Tanzania \cite{Edward2024OralHealthTZ,inchingolo2025ai_dentistry_review}. The central premise is that, even in the absence of comprehensive labeled dental datasets for fine-tuning, the integration of semantic retrieval over curated clinical protocols and guideline sources with pre-trained multimodal models can improve diagnostic reliability, interpretability, and contextual suitability compared to conventional systems that rely solely on internal model parameters \cite{lewis2020retrieval,huang2023multimodal,schwendicke2022ai_global}. Rather than developing new models through training, this research focuses on architecting a system that orchestrates existing models and grounds their outputs in authoritative knowledge sources.
	
	\subsection{Research Objectives}
	The specific objectives are as follows:
	
	\begin{itemize}
		\item \textbf{O1: System Architecture Design.} Design an orchestrated multimodal pipeline combining vision models, retrieval components, and language models  (See Figure ~\ref{fig:modules_highlight}): \\
		(a) a vision model abstraction layer supporting multiple providers (local: LLaVA, Gemma3, BiomedCLIP; cloud: GPT-4V, Claude, Groq, Gemini) for extracting clinically relevant features from dental radiographs, enabling easy switching to accommodate varying resource constraints; \\
		(b) a text-based language model layer for synthesizing clinical reasoning over vision findings, patient history, and retrieved guideline content, with pluggable provider support; \\
		(c) a RAG pipeline that dynamically retrieves relevant guideline excerpts from a curated knowledge base at inference time \cite{lewis2020retrieval,huang2023multimodal}; \\
		(d) an orchestration layer coordinating the end-to-end diagnostic workflow, managing data flow between components, and enforcing clinical validation rules (e.g., tooth number consistency). 
		
		
		\item \textbf{O2: Knowledge Base Construction and Retrieval Optimization.} Construct and integrate a curated knowledge base comprising Tanzania-specific policy documents, including the Standard Treatment Guideline (STG) from the Ministry of Health, international dental guidelines, peer-reviewed evidence, and clinical recommendations for oral health \cite{world2024global,Edward2024OralHealthTZ,tanzania_oral_health_policy}. Implement and evaluate chunking strategies, embedding model selection (nomic-embed-text, MedEmbed), and retrieval mechanisms to optimize semantic search within the RAG pipeline for clinical accuracy and relevance.
		
		\item \textbf{O3: Production-Ready Prototype Implementation.} Implement a production-ready  system using open-source frameworks (FastAPI, LangChain, Chroma, PostgreSQL) with a modular architecture that supports multiple model providers (Ollama, OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq, Google Gemini). Demonstrate end-to-end functionality from input (radiograph and patient data) to output (diagnostic statement and treatment recommendation with guideline citations) \cite{lewis2020retrieval,litjens2017survey}. Integrate this system with a Next.js-based frontend interface for improved clinical usability and workflow integration.
		
		\item \textbf{O4: Comparative Model Evaluation.} Evaluate and compare multiple vision model architectures (local: LLaVA 7B/13B, Gemma3 4B/12B, BiomedCLIP, Florence-2; cloud: GPT-4V, Claude 3.5, Groq Llama vision models, Gemini 2.0) within the RAG-enhanced system, assessing diagnostic accuracy, inference speed, resource utilization (RAM, disk), token consumption, and cost-effectiveness across different deployment scenarios \cite{Dashti2024DLCariesUmbrella,Arzani2025AICariesUmbrella,MADANKUMAR20261}.
		
		\item \textbf{O5: Deployment Feasibility Analysis for Resource-Constrained Settings.} Analyze deployment feasibility and cost-effectiveness for Tanzania's healthcare context, including infrastructure requirements, operational costs, hardware specifications, and suitability for three-tier deployment scenarios (rural clinics with limited connectivity, district hospitals with moderate resources, urban facilities with reliable infrastructure) \cite{Edward2024OralHealthTZ,tanzania_oral_health_policy}. Provide evidence-based recommendations for optimal model selection and system configuration based on local constraints.
		
		\item \textbf{O6: Retrieval Quality and Clinical Grounding Assessment.} Evaluate the quality, relevance, and consistency of retrieved knowledge snippets in supporting transparent, guideline grounded diagnostic explanations. Assess the system's ability to reduce hallucinations through explicit citation and evidence based reasoning,  and qualitative assessment of output grounding \cite{lewis2020retrieval,ji2023survey}.
	\end{itemize}
	
