	\subsection{Research Questions}
	These objectives give rise to the following research questions:
	
	\begin{itemize}
		\item \textbf{RQ1: Architectural Design and Component Integration.} How can a modular, RAG-based architecture be designed to effectively combine pre-trained vision models, language models, and retrieval mechanisms for dental diagnostic reasoning and treatment recommendation? What interface contracts and data flow patterns enable seamless integration of heterogeneous components while maintaining system reliability and extensibility?
		
		\item \textbf{RQ2: Vision Model Selection and Cost \& Performance Tradeoffs.} How do different pre-trained vision model architectures (local vs. cloud, varying sizes, medical specific vs. general purpose) compare in diagnostic accuracy for dental pathology detection, tooth identification, and radiographic feature extraction? What are the tradeoffs between inference speed, resource utilization, cost, and accuracy across models, and how do these inform optimal model choices for different deployment scenarios in resource-constrained settings? \cite{Dashti2024DLCariesUmbrella,Arzani2025AICariesUmbrella,lewis2020retrieval,Wada2025RAGRadiology}
		
		\item \textbf{RQ3: Retrieval Quality and Evidence Grounding.} How relevant, consistent, and evidence-aligned are the knowledge snippets retrieved by the RAG pipeline when supporting diagnostic explanations? To what extent does retrieval augmentation reduce hallucinations and improve factual accuracy compared to non-RAG baselines? How do different chunking strategies, embedding models, and retrieval parameters affect the quality of retrieved evidence and subsequent diagnostic recommendations? \cite{lewis2020retrieval,ji2023survey}
		
		\item \textbf{RQ4: Regional Guideline Integration and Deployment Optimization.} How can region-specific clinical guidelines (Tanzanian Ministry of Health protocols) be effectively structured, chunked, and indexed within the RAG knowledge base to support context-aware recommendations? What deployment configurations (hardware specifications, model selection, caching strategies, fallback mechanisms) are most suitable for Tanzania's three-tier healthcare infrastructure, considering connectivity limitations, power reliability, and budget constraints? \cite{Edward2024OralHealthTZ,tanzania_oral_health_policy,schwendicke2022ai_global}
		
		\item \textbf{RQ5: System-Level Performance and Clinical Utility.} How does the end-to-end RAG-based system perform on metrics of clinical utility, including diagnostic agreement with expert interpretation, appropriateness of treatment recommendations, citation accuracy, and response latency? What are the primary failure modes and limitations of the system when applied to real-world clinical scenarios, and how can these be mitigated through architectural refinements or workflow integration?
	\end{itemize}
