\chapter{Implementation and Experimental Setup}
\label{chap:implementation}

This chapter describes the practical realisation of the RAG-based
multimodal clinical decision-support system designed in Chapter~\ref{chap:design}.
It specifies the development environment, software dependencies, and
technology stack used to build the system (Section~\ref{sec:stack});
details the datasets and preprocessing procedures applied to periapical
radiograph images and clinical guideline documents
(Section~\ref{sec:datasets}); documents the proof-of-concept
implementation, including the backend API, vision layer, RAG pipeline,
and clinical reasoning module (Section~\ref{sec:implementation}); and
defines the experimental setup and evaluation methodology used to assess
the system (Section~\ref{sec:eval_method}).  Where relevant,
implementation decisions are cross-referenced to the design principles
established in Chapter~\ref{chap:design}.

