\paragraph{Confidence scores.}
The \texttt{diagnostic\_confidence} value is a model-intrinsic
self-reported metric representing the model's self-assessed certainty
based on image quality, feature clarity, and training-data similarity.
It is \emph{not} calibrated against external ground truth; its
interpretation and limitations are discussed further in Chapter~\ref{chap:results}.

\subsection{Experimental Protocol}
\label{subsec:protocol}

All vision model evaluations use the same periapical test radiograph
under identical conditions: patient~ID~=~3, chief complaint
\textit{``sharp pain on the right side of the lower jaw''}, tooth
number~=~47.  Each model was called twice independently via
\texttt{POST /api/vision/analyze\_image}; reported metrics are averaged
across the two runs to reduce cold-start variance.  The multi-model
benchmark endpoint (\texttt{POST /api/vision/test\_vision\_models}) is
additionally used to obtain a single-shot cross-model snapshot under
truly identical conditions.

For RAG evaluation, the query \textit{``What is the management for a
patient with toothache?''} is submitted per LLM provider via
\texttt{POST /api/rag/answer\_question} with MMR retrieval ($k{=}8$).
Providers tested include Ollama (llama3.1:8b, llama3:8b, gemma3:4b),
Groq (llama-3.3-70b), Google Gemini (2.5-flash, 2.5-pro), Claude
(claude-3-haiku), and OpenAI (gpt-4o).  For end-to-end CDSS evaluation,
four vision+LLM combinations are tested via
\texttt{POST /api/cdss/provide\_final\_recommendation}, and all providers
are tested on the image-free pathway.

