\section{Summary}
\label{sec:ch4_summary}
% ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This chapter has described the implementation and experimental setup of
the DentoBase system.  The backend is built on Python~3.13+ and FastAPI,
with PostgreSQL for relational clinical data and ChromaDB for semantic
guideline retrieval, implementing the architectural design from
Chapter~\ref{chap:design} using exclusively open-source components.  The knowledge base encodes
the 618-page Tanzania STG in approximately 1\,200--1\,400 ChromaDB
chunks retrieved via MMR ($k{=}8$, $\mathit{fetch\_k}{=}20$,
$\lambda{=}1.0$), with stable page-coverage behaviour confirmed across
all LLM providers tested.  Eleven vision models spanning three hardware
tiers (\textit{minimal}, \textit{recommended}, \textit{cloud}) and
multiple LLM providers are supported through common abstraction
interfaces, with all provider switching controlled via runtime
configuration APIs.

The evaluation methodology addresses the absence of ground-truth labels
by focusing on system-level performance metrics (inference latency,
token throughput, RAM usage, cost), output quality indicators (schema
validity, confidence scores, tooth identification), and qualitative
clinical utility assessment.  Four experimental conditions, vision-only,
image-free RAG, non-RAG multimodal, and the proposed RAG-enhanced
pipeline; provide the structure for the comparative analysis presented
in Chapter~\ref{chap:results}.



