\chapter{Results and Analysis}
\label{chap:results}

This chapter presents the empirical findings from the evaluation of the RAG-based multimodal clinical decision support system described in
Chapters~\ref{chap:design} and~\ref{chap:implementation}. Following the Design
Science Research methodology, the evaluation addresses the research questions
formulated in Chapter~\ref{chap:introduction} through systematic quantitative
and qualitative analysis. Throughout, the emphasis is placed on
\emph{system-level behaviour} rather than pixel-level diagnostic accuracy,
reflecting the absence of expert-labelled ground truth for the radiograph
dataset.

The chapter is organised into five sections. Section~\ref{sec:results_vision}
presents a quantitative comparison of eleven vision models. Section~\ref{sec:results_rag}
evaluates the RAG pipeline's retrieval consistency and LLM output reliability.
Section~\ref{sec:results_cdss} presents end-to-end CDSS results through
representative case studies. Section~\ref{sec:results_deployment} analyses
deployment feasibility for Tanzania's three-tier healthcare infrastructure.
Section~\ref{sec:results_discussion} synthesises findings against the research
questions, identifies failure modes, and surfaces key insights that inform
Chapter~\ref{chap:conclusion}.

The primary test case throughout is a periapical radiograph of tooth~\#47,
patient~3 (40-year-old female, chief complaint: \textit{``sharp pain on the right
side of the lower jaw''}, two SOAP-format clinical notes on record, these records indicate that the patient has had prior visits with complain of mild pain on the same side of today's complain, the patient has had a tooth filling on the same side prior).Experimental logs are available in \texttt{evaluation\_results.json}

