\subsection{Pharmacological Accuracy}

All six successful providers correctly reproduced the STG-2021 first-line
analgesic regimen (paracetamol 1g PO 8-hourly for 3~days; ibuprofen 400mg
8-hourly; diclofenac 50mg 8-hourly) and the antibiotic regimen (ampicillin +
cloxacillin FDC 500mg PO 8-hourly for 5~days plus metronidazole 400mg 8-hourly
for 5~days), including the penicillin-allergy substitution (erythromycin 500mg
PO 6-hourly for 5~days, page~387). Drug names, routes, doses, and durations
matched STG entries exactly in all cases.

One nuance: llama3:8b additionally included amoxicillin + clavulanic acid 625mg
12-hourly, drawn from page~391 (alveolar osteitis). This page appeared in the
retrieved chunk set due to the high-diversity MMR configuration. The recommendation
is genuine and guideline-compliant, this represents \emph{retrieval-induced
context breadth} rather than hallucination, but illustrates that $\lambda{=}1.0$
can surface adjacent, not strictly query-applicable, content.

